<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Imagine a group battle 5 wizards vs 5 warriors, is there any question who will win?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Taro">Taro</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 3:12 p.m. 11/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Imagine a group battle 5 wizards vs 5 warriors, is there any question who will win?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=705" TARGET=_self>Imagine a group battle 5 wizards vs 5 warriors, is there any question who will win?</A> (-Nafgar[CC])
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Actually, with the amazing hp the warriors have, they would probably win. The wizards would, of course, dump huge amounts of mana and wipe out the first warrior in record time. The second one would probably die too, but, mana would start to run low about this time or maybe even after the third warrior, but 5 wizards wielding staves and no magic will not win against even 2 warriors in combat equipment. That's the weakness to wizards, they run out of steam, melees don't, as long as they stay alive. And as you said, with a cleric, warriors will be as useful(more useful?) than a wizard, as they will be able to dish out constant damage, never stopping, and will be healed a lot so it wouldn't be so easy to unload spells and kill him quickly. Also, with the types of magic resistance things that are supposedly in the game, warriors might have a better chance against spellcasters. About rogues though, since I don't know a thing about how backstab, and hide and sneak work with players, I can't have a real opinion about that.

<P>Taro
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
